{{Infobox language |name=Bodo Parja |altname=Jharia |states=[[India]] |region=[[Koraput District]], [[Odisha]] |speakers=50,000 |date=2001 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Indo-European |fam2=[[Indo-Iranian languages|Indo-Iranian]] |fam3=[[Indo-Aryan languages|Indo-Aryan]] |fam4=[[Eastern Indo-Aryan languages|Eastern]] |fam5=[[Oriya languages|Oriya]] |script=[[Oriya script]] |iso3=bdv |glotto=bodo1266 |glottorefname=Bodo Parja }}
'''Bodo Parja''' or '''Jharia''' is a language spoken in [[Odisha]] and is closely related to [[Odia language|Odia]] but not intelligible with it. Most speakers have low proficiency in the [[Adivasi]] [[Odia language|Oriya]] used at market.<ref name="e18" />
