{{Infobox language |name = Eritrean Sign Language |region = [[Eritrea]] |created = 2005 |creator = Eritrean National Association of the Deaf |posteriori = [[A priori language]] |familycolor = conlang |family=To purge the existing sign language of its foreign roots |iso3 = none |glotto=none }}
'''Eritrean Sign Language''' is an artificial [[sign language]] lexicon of [[Eritrea]]. It is designed to replace the existing sign lexicon, which developed since sign language was introduced in 1955 and was based on [[Swedish Sign Language|Swedish]] and [[Finnish Sign Language]], with ASL-based [[Sudanese sign languages|Sudanese]] influences.<ref name="Eritrean Sign Language">{{cite web | url=http://www.editora-arara-azul.com.br/ebooks/catalogo/30.pdf | title=Construction in Eritrean Sign Language | publisher = [[California State University]] | accessdate=December 2006}}</ref>
