{{Infobox language |name=Southern Uzbek |nativename=''اوزبیکچه, اوزبیکی, اوزبیک تورکچه'' |states= [[Afghanistan]], [[Uzbekistan]], [[Turkmenistan]], [[Iran]], [[Tajikistan]], [[China]], [[Saudi Arabia]], [[Pakistan]] |ethnicity=[[Uzbeks]] |speakers = 4.2 million |date = 2017 |ref = e18 |familycolor = Altaic |fam1=[[Turkic languages|Turkic]] |fam2=[[Common Turkic languages|Common Turkic]] |fam3=[[Karluk languages|Karluk]]<ref name="Newton2014">{{cite book|author=Scott Newton|title=Law and the Making of the Soviet World: The Red Demiurge|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3JWLBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA232&dq=Chagatai+%22Old+Uzbek%22+official&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi8sMj0tO_KAhXI1R4KHe_2DEgQ6AEIIzAB#v=onepage&q=Chagatai%20%22Old%20Uzbek%22%20official&f=false|date=20 November 2014|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-317-92978-9|pages=232–}}</ref> |ancestor=[[Middle Turkic languages|Middle Turkic]] |ancestor2=[[Khorezmian language (Turkic)|Khorezmian]] |ancestor3=[[Chagatai language|Chagatai]] |nation= {{AFG}} (3rd official language) |script=[[Arabic script|Arabic]] |iso3=uzs |lingua=44-AAB-da, db |glotto=sout2699 |glottorefname=Southern Uzbek |notice=IPA |minority={{plainlist| *{{flag|China}} }} |agency = [[Afghan Ministry of Education]] }}
'''Southern Uzbek''', also known as ''Afghan Uzbek'', is the southern variant of the [[Uzbek language]] and an official language of Afghanistan where it is based and has up to 4.2 million speakers. It uses the [[Perso-Arabic]] writing system in contrast to the language variant of [[Uzbekistan]].
It shares the same [[macrolanguage]] with the northern variant spoken in Uzbekistan and its spoken form is intelligible to the northern variant to a certain degree. However it has differences in grammar and much more loan words from [[Dari language (Afghanistan)|Afghan Persian]], which many of the Southern Uzbek speakers are proficient in. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ethnologue.com/language/uzs|title=Uzbek, Southern|publisher=}}</ref>
== Southern Uzbek Alphabet == [[File:Adib-i sani.jpg|thumb|upright=0.54|A 1911 text in Southern Uzbek]] {{Main|Uzbek alphabet}}
Southern Uzbek is written using the Perso-Arabic writing system called ''Arab Yozuv'' ("Arab Script"). Although it contains the same 32 letters which are used in [[Persian language|Persian]], it pronounces many of them in another way.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Uzbek_language&oldid=843343606|title=Uzbek language|date=28 May 2018|publisher=|via=Wikipedia}}</ref>
