{{Use Indian English|date=June 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=June 2017}} '''Venkataramiah Sitaramiah''', also known as '''VeeCee''' (2 October 1899 &ndash; 1983), is a [[Kannada]]-language writer who received the National [[Sahitya Akademi Award]] in 1973.
Sitaramiah was born in Boodigeri village of Bangalore district. He earned a B.A (1920) and a M.A (1922) from the [[Maharaja College of Mysore]]. He was professor at various colleges in Karnataka State and principal of [[Arts and Science College, Honnavar]] from 1964 to 1968.{{Citation needed|date= October 2012}}
==His work== * ''Nelau-Belaku'' * ''Aralu-baralu'' (Earned the National Sahitya Akademi Award). * ''Beladingalu'' * ''Agrah'' * ''Major barber''
